caption: Table 1: Comparison of classification accuracy of the two-stage model.
description: This table presents the top-1 classification accuracy (Precision@1) results for two different two-stage recommendation models, TS and H-TS, evaluated across three different numbers of retrieved items (K=40, K=80, K=120). The results are shown for two datasets, Mind and Movie.  The H-TS model (Harmonized Two-Stage Model), which focuses on aligning training and inference data distributions, generally shows slightly better performance than the TS (Two-Stage Model) across all settings.

caption: Table 1: Comparison of classification accuracy of the two-stage model.
description: This table compares the top-1 classification accuracy (Precision@1) of two different two-stage recommender system models (TS and H-TS) on two datasets (Mind and Movie).  The results show the accuracy for different numbers of retrieved items (K) in the first stage. The H-TS model, which uses a harmonized training distribution for the ranker, generally performs better than the standard TS model.
